  "id": "BIT-ceph-2022-0670",
  "details": "A flaw was found in Openstack manilla owning a Ceph File system \"share\", which enables the owner to read/write any manilla share or entire file system. The vulnerability is due to a bug in the \"volumes\" plugin in Ceph Manager. This allows an attacker to compromise Confidentiality and Integrity of a file system. Fixed in RHCS 5.2 and Ceph 17.2.2.",
